Continuation root cause + fix (2026-05-25, the brick wall): agents 'do one part then stop' because every programming agent reads ONLY tool calls and their outputs — an assistant message ending in prose with no tool call IS the turn ending, and the harness halts there. A summary/recap is therefore a stop. Fix shipped across all three instruction surfaces (gm a5b162ac SKILL.md+AGENTS.md, rs-plugkit c15f2db entry.rs+verify.rs): while chain in-flight (phase!=COMPLETE OR prd_pending>0) NEVER end a turn in prose, NEVER summarize; only plugkit returning phase=COMPLETE AND prd_pending=0 authorizes a prose-only turn; before any stop/summary dispatch phase-status and recheck. Tool-agnostic — depends only on the verb spool, no hook/tool-specific feature. Spawnpoint diagnosis (ccsniff 627dff5f): subagents invoked via Agent(subagent_type=gm:gm) returned prose 'Done. Updated...' that the parent treated as closure. Two Claude-Code-specific mechanisms found and de-fanged: rs-plugkit lib.rs:123 permissionDecisionReason + session_start policy named Skill(gm:gm)/Agent(gm:gm); both rewritten to name the portable spool dispatch. The wasm_hooks exports (pre_tool_use/post_tool_use/session_start emitting hookSpecificOutput/permissionDecision Claude-hook JSON) are dead ABI — zero spool-watcher callers — left as harmless dead code; the portability-violating agent-facing TEXT is eliminated.